Note that this R package is just an interface
	R <--> xgobi
	R <--> xgvis
to the two (related) programs xgobi and xgvis.

You must install these independently and can get them via
	~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
	http://www.research.att.com/areas/stat/xgobi/
	~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Note that within the next several months,
xgobi (& xgvis) will be replaced by the more flexible and modern
`GGobi' and its tools, see  http://www.ggobi.org/
			    ---------------------
